snippet.title: Ukraine moves against insurgents in the east
snippet.description: Russia announced new military exercises Thursday involving ground and air forces near its border with Ukraine, swiftly responding to a Ukrainian operation to drive pro-Russia insurgents out of occupied buildings in the country's tumultuous east.

snippet.title: Clashes spread across eastern Ukraine as Russia begins military drills on border
snippet.description: Skirmishes between Ukrainian security forces, pro-Russia activists and local protesters continue to spread.

snippet.title: Bloodied shirt, unwashed fork: JPII relics abound
snippet.description: Inside a chapel on the edge of Rome, a nun uses a key to open a wooden wall panel, revealing a hidden niche. Behind glass and stitched loosely to supporting backing hangs a relic of holy suffering: the bullet-pocked, bloodstained undershirt that John Paul II was wearing when a gunman shot him in the stomach in St. Peter's Square.

snippet.title: Photos of the day
snippet.description: China fashion, London's Globe Theatre, a breakaway Antarctic iceberg, Sewol ferry victim search, ice breaking on the Great Lakes, a New York cat cafe and more.

snippet.title: Clashes in east Ukraine leave at least 2 dead
snippet.description: Ukrainian troops moved against pro-Russia forces in eastern Ukraine on Thursday, killing at least two of them in clashes at checkpoints, both sides said. Russian President Vladimir Putin decried what he described as a "punitive operation."

snippet.title: 'The Americans' recap: 'Martial Eagle' sounds better than it feels
snippet.description: In "The Americans," the promise of heaven may be more dangerous than the torments of hell.

snippet.title: India goes to the polls
snippet.description: On Monday, April 7, 2014, Indians begin voting in the world's biggest election ever. With an electorate of 814 million, the voting is set to take place in stages over five weeks.

snippet.title: 5 ways to help heroin addicts
snippet.description: With heroin overdoses on the rise, advocates want more access to treatment, and Good Samaritan laws.

snippet.title: Connecticut man charged in Yale hoax threat
snippet.description: A Connecticut man has been charged with making a call during the Thanksgiving holidays in which he falsely claimed an armed man was on the way to shoot up Yale University, police said Wednesday.

snippet.title: Venezuela's economic crisis catches up with malls
snippet.description: Staring through a glass storefront at the Sambil shopping mall, Aleimar Sanchez sees more than a struggling business in the near-empty shelves of a Casio electronics store. She sees a country in sad decline.
